# Cornerstone environment template.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. NEVER commit a real `.env` (see .gitignore).
# The Lovable build committed live keys; this build keeps all secrets out of source.
#
# For local development, run `npx supabase start` — it prints the local anon key and
# service_role key. See docs/dev-setup.md.

# --- Frontend (Vite, exposed to the browser — publishable values only) ---
# These are bundled into the client build. Only ever put publishable (anon) values here.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-local-anon-key

# --- Edge functions / server-side (NOT exposed to the browser) ---
# Set as Supabase function secrets / environment secrets, not in the FE build.
# Listed here for completeness; populated per environment via the secret manager.
# Locally, `supabase start` provides these to functions automatically.
# SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- Integration credentials (per-environment secrets) ---
# See docs/lovable_pattern_inventory.md §4. Never commit real values.
# Forth (PLSA processor — per-tenant creds are encrypted at rest in the DB; these are the
# platform-level API credentials used by the forth-* edge functions):
# FORTH_CLIENT_ID=
# FORTH_API_KEY=
# DocuSeal (e-signature):
# DOCUSEAL_API_TOKEN=
# DOCUSEAL_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Dialpad (telephony — click-to-call, screen-pop, call webhooks):
# DIALPAD_API_TOKEN=
# DIALPAD_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# DIALPAD_DEFAULT_USER_ID=
